Caesar tells us that he had 80 transports for his two legions. By the storin 12 ships were lost. These 12 were probably transpone, as they were at enchon and hence more ex- posed to danger. That would leave 68. From the two that were , separated from the fleet, about 300 men were landed. At that rate, in the 68 ships there must have been 10,2oo men. As the legions were without heavy baggage‚ there would have been no servants exeepting sor the officers.
